#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.103"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.103:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.103:0.2"
msgid "11. Valāhakavagga "
msgstr "11. Clouds "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.103:0.3"
msgid "103. Kumbhasutta "
msgstr "103. Pots "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.103:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, kumbhā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four pots. "

msgctxt "an4.103:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
# NOTE: I’ve reversed the sequence of each pair so they match with the explanations.
msgctxt "an4.103:1.3"
msgid "Tuccho pihito, pūro vivaṭo, tuccho vivaṭo, pūro pihito—"
msgstr "~Covered but hollow, ~uncovered but full, ~uncovered and hollow, and ~covered and full. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
msgctxt "an4.103:1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kumbhā. "
msgstr "These are the four pots. "

msgctxt "an4.103:1.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kumbhūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "In the same way, these four people similar to pots are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.103:1.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "an4.103:1.7"
msgid "Tuccho pihito, pūro vivaṭo, tuccho vivaṭo, pūro pihito. "
msgstr "~Covered but hollow, ~uncovered but full, ~uncovered and hollow, and ~covered and full. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.103:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti pihito? "
msgstr "And how is a person covered but hollow? "

msgctxt "an4.103:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a person is impressive when going out and coming back, when looking ahead and aside, when bending and extending the limbs, and when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes. "

msgctxt "an4.103:2.3"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "But they don’t truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "an4.103:2.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti pihito. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is covered but hollow. "

msgctxt "an4.103:2.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho tuccho pihito; "
msgstr "That person is like a pot that’s covered but hollow, I say. "

msgctxt "an4.103:2.6"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.103:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti vivaṭo? "
msgstr "And how is a person uncovered but full? "

msgctxt "an4.103:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a person is not impressive … "

msgctxt "an4.103:3.3"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "But they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an4.103:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti vivaṭo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.103:3.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho pūro vivaṭo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.103:3.6"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.103:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti vivaṭo? "
msgstr "And how is a person uncovered and hollow? "

msgctxt "an4.103:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa na pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a person is not impressive … "

msgctxt "an4.103:4.3"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "Nor do they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an4.103:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo tuccho hoti vivaṭo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.103:4.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho tuccho vivaṭo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.103:4.6"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.105, sc5
msgctxt "an4.103:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti pihito? "
msgstr "And how is a person covered and full? "

msgctxt "an4.103:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa pāsādikaṃ hoti abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a person is impressive … "

msgctxt "an4.103:5.3"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an4.103:5.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo pūro hoti pihito. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.103:5.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, kumbho pūro pihito; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.103:5.6"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.103:5.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro kumbhūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These four people similar to pots are found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.103:5.8"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

